<!-- l. 32 --><p class="indent" style="margin: 0; padding: 0; box-sizing: border-box; margin-bottom: 1em;">   This has led to a common misconception: that the <span class="ec-lmtt-10" style="margin: 0; padding: 0; box-sizing: border-box;">-Wall </span>flag offers developers sufficient protection against
CWE-457. However, this is not the case. In this SwA tip, we explore some common situations where <span class="ec-lmtt-10" style="margin: 0; padding: 0; box-sizing: border-box;">-Wall </span>fails to
detect the use of uninitialized variables.

</p>   
